{
  "texts": [
    "This oversight gap can lead to security and privacy vulnerabilities, making a more expansive and inclusive review essential to ensure these algorithms are safe and effective before widespread use.",
    "A multistakeholder assessment is crucial to validating these algorithms both before and after deployment 46, 47.",
    "Currently, little responsibility is placed on AI developers to predict, mitigate, and report the risks their algorithms may cause.",
    "There is no established accountability chain for algorithmic malpractice, leaving clinicians exposed to liability, especially when AI systems are used to identify and track medical errors.",
    "For instance, if a radiologist flagged by an AIenabled QP review later contributes to a wrong-side procedure due to inaccurate AI analysis, the implications for liability are unclear."
  ]
}